Create a dashboard file using Streamlit to display test results. I want the following:

Total number of test cases

A button to run each individual test case and another to run all test cases

Number of passed and failed tests

A pie chart showing the percentage of passed/failed tests

A detailed table for each test case including: test name, status (pass/fail), and execution time

The data can be a list of dictionaries in Python. Please make the interface clean and easy to understand.
The folder struct must follow this format:
mcp-playwright-cx/
|-- requirements.txt
|-- page
|   |-- __init__.py
|   |-- login_page.py
    |-- customer_page.py
    |-- Knowledge_page.py
|--tests/

|   |-- pytest.ini
|   |-- test_Login
       |-- Login_successfully.py
       |-- Invalid_email.py
       |-- Invalid_pass.py
       |-- blank_email.py
       |-- blank_pass.py
    |-- test_Customer_page
        |-- TC_01.py
        |-- TC_02.py
        |-- TC_03.py
        ....
    |-- test_Knowledge_page
        |-- Delete_file_successfully.py
        |-- Delete_file_cancel.py
        |-- Download_file_successfully.py
        |-- Download_file_cancel.py
        ....
        
|--README.md
|--Dashboard

Replace the file.py names in the structure with the names of the test cases.